# Software and Tools Used

The project was developed using a set of powerful Python-based tools and libraries for data processing, machine learning, visualization, and deployment. These technologies provide the foundation for efficient model development, analysis, and application deployment.

### 1. Anaconda Navigator

A desktop graphical user interface used to launch applications and manage Python packages and environments for data science.

**Official Website:**
https://www.anaconda.com/download

---

### 2. PyCharm

An Integrated Development Environment (IDE) specifically designed for Python programming, offering intelligent code completion, debugging, and project management tools.

**Official Website:**
https://www.jetbrains.com/pycharm/

---

### 3. NumPy

A fundamental Python library for numerical computing, providing support for large, multi-dimensional arrays and mathematical operations.

**Documentation:**
https://numpy.org/doc/stable/

---

### 4. Pandas

A powerful data manipulation and analysis library used for handling structured datasets efficiently.

**Documentation:**
https://pandas.pydata.org/docs/

---

### 5. Scikit-learn

A popular machine learning library that provides classification, regression, clustering, preprocessing, and model evaluation algorithms.

**Documentation:**
https://scikit-learn.org/stable/

---

### 6. Matplotlib

A comprehensive plotting library used to create high-quality graphs, charts, and visualizations.

**Documentation:**
https://matplotlib.org/stable/

---

### 7. Seaborn

A statistical data visualization library built on top of Matplotlib that provides attractive and informative graphics.

**Documentation:**
https://seaborn.pydata.org/

---

### 8. Flask

A lightweight Python web framework used to develop and deploy the machine learning web application.

**Documentation:**
https://flask.palletsprojects.com/

---

## Installation

Install all required Python libraries using:

```bash
pip install numpy pandas scikit-learn xgboost matplotlib seaborn flask joblib
```
